{
  "texts": [
    "The description of mesoscale behavior requires more physical quantities.",
    "The \"mesoscale\" characteristics of DBM include: (i) in terms of scale, between micro and macro, connecting micro and macro; (ii) in terms of functionality, surpassing NS in describing discrete/non-equilibrium effects, but weaker than MD.",
    "In DBM, the corresponding solutions to the six basic scientific problems proposed in Section 2 are as follows: f -f (0)For problem (i), add physical quantities based on the definition of non-conserved kinetic moments according to the degree of discreteness/non-equilibrium.",
    "In response to problem (ii), phase space description methods based on non-conserved moments of, morphological and other behavioral feature quantities are introduced.",
    "In response to problem (iii), the model construction no longer relies on continuity and near equilibrium assumptions."
  ]
}